Coming to the theatre

   Acces

   Address : 1, place du Trocadéro - 75116 Paris

   Persons with reduced mobility: access through the Place de Varsovie
   See the map

   plan_acces_2018.jpg

   acces3.jpg

   Safety recommendations

   logo_vigipirate_securite_renforcee-risque_attentat-01.png

   The reinforced Vigipirate plan “Reinforced security – Risk of attack”
   is applicable on all of the Palais de Chaillot. In this respect,
   numerous measures have been taken to ensure the security of the public
   welcomed at the theatre. Namely:
     * Checking bag contents is systematically in operation at the theatre
       entrance. Any large bag, including a bag the size of cabin luggage,
       will not be accepted in the theatre.
     * A metal detection is also carried out

   We thank you for respecting the instructions that will be given to you
   on your arrival.

   Due to these new constraints, thank you for arriving at the theatre at
   least 30 minutes prior to the performance.

   Any person who refuses the control check will not be given access to
   the establishment.

